This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on spatial understanding for mobile robots. The use of deep networks for semantic mapping suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The probabilistic nature of the model and its ability to perform uncertain reasoning suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of complex spatial relations and graphs suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of natural language processing and semantic understanding suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
